										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Attila BlascsÃ¡k is one of CodeBerryâ€™s first users, who successfully changed his career and became a web developer after studying with us. We had a chat with Attila about how he got here, what he learned and the difficulties of finding a job as a junior developer.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}"><strong>Attila BlascsÃ¡k</strong> is one of <a href="https://codeberryschool.com/en/" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="external">CodeBerry</a>â€™s first users, who successfully changed his career and became a web developer after studying with us. We had a chat with Attila about how he got here, what he learned about programming, and the difficulties of finding a job as a junior developer.Â </span></p>
<h3><strong>When someone asked about your profession a few months ago, how did you answer?Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;I used to say my job is networking at IT Services, meaning that I helped big companies join the internet. Our task spread from assuring the router arrived at the customer to actually making it work.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">I used to say my job is networking at <a href="https://www.it-services.hu/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener external" data-wpel-link="external">IT Services,</a> meaning that I helped big companies join the internet. Our task spread from assuring the router arrived at the customer to actually making it work.Â </span></p>
<h3><strong>And what is your answer now?</strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at <a href="https://www.epam.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener external" data-wpel-link="external">EPAM</a>. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface.<a href="https://codeberryschool.com/blog/en/a-brief-introduction-to-web-development/" data-wpel-link="external" target="_blank" rel="external"> I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript</a> on a daily basis.Â </span></p>
<p><a href="https://codeberryschool.com/en/all-access-self-paced" target="_blank" rel="noopener external" data-wpel-link="external"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-12254 size-full" src="https://codeberryschool.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-1.png" alt="" width="1024" height="340" srcset="/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-1.png 1024w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-1-300x100.png 300w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-1-768x255.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<h3><strong>That sounds great! So, programming wasnâ€™t really a new task for you, was it? Did you encounter coding earlier?</strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">Yes, I actually started using HTML and CSS during elementary school. Later in high school, we used Python all the time, relying on an antique book. I had to quit doing it because the libraries cited by the author didnâ€™t exist anymore, so the tasks were unsolvable. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f642.png" alt="ğŸ™‚" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></span></p>
<h3><strong>Where did the idea of web development come from?Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">During my senior year of high school, two guys approached me, saying they needed web developers for their startup. Back then I had no clue about what I was about to dive into, but I said yes and I soon got the hang of it. Eventually, we finished the project, but web development had caught my attention, so I continued learning it on my own. Finally, I ran into a dead-end in spring, when I felt I canâ€™t go on alone, I need a teacher. Thatâ€™s when I found you. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f642.png" alt="ğŸ™‚" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />Â </span></p>
<p><a href="https://codeberryschool.com/en/all-access-self-paced" target="_blank" rel="noopener external" data-wpel-link="external"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-12018 size-full" src="https://codeberryschool.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Testimonial-1.png" alt="" width="1024" height="340" srcset="/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Testimonial-1.png 1024w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Testimonial-1-300x100.png 300w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Testimonial-1-768x255.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<h3><strong>How long have you been studying with CodeBerry?Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">Since June 2016.Â </span></p>
<h3><strong>And how did you like it, what were the advantages?Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">To be honest, there wasn&#8217;t a tremendous amount of new information, but the course was great for recollecting my knowledge. The mentors helped me a lot â€“ that was probably one of the best things in it. Having someone to discuss your problems with is a huge advantage.Â </span></p>
<p><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-8289" src="https://codeberryschool.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1-1024x768.jpg" alt="You can learn programming online at Codeberry" width="1024" height="768" srcset="/blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1-1024x768.jpg 1024w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1-300x225.jpg 300w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1-768x576.jpg 768w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1-1080x810.jpg 1080w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/code-4918187_1920-1.jpg 1920w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></p>
<p>Thatâ€™s good to hear. Now itâ€™s the beginning of autumn, that means youâ€™ve gained enough knowledge in 3 months to find a job.</p>
<h3><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}"><strong>How long did it take you to find one?</strong> (The interview took place in September 2016 â€“ ed.)Â </span></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">Actually, I havenâ€™t even decided to start looking for a job yet. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f642.png" alt="ğŸ™‚" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />Â </span><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">I created a LinkedIn profile, where I stated I was studying to become a junior developer and added my new skills too. Two weeks later EPAM contacted me.Â I was going to create a portfolio before contemplating looking for a job, but EPAM was faster. They invited me to an interview right away.Â </span></p>
<h3><strong>I wanted to ask you if the search was difficult, but I guess we can skip this question.Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">Yes. (Laughs)Â </span></p>
<p><a href="https://codeberryschool.com/en/all-access-self-paced" target="_blank" rel="noopener external" data-wpel-link="external"><img loading="lazy" class="aligncenter wp-image-12255 size-full" src="https://codeberryschool.com/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-2.png" alt="" width="1024" height="340" srcset="/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-2.png 1024w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-2-300x100.png 300w, /blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/Self-paced-2-768x255.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></a></p>
<h3><strong>What is the next step for you? What direction are you taking?Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">React environment is my current favourite, I would like to learn more about it in the upcoming period. Itâ€™s also a huge dream of mine to teach programming in some form. Giving lectures or taking part in some more specific program, I donâ€™t know yet, nor do I know how itâ€™s going to happen, but Iâ€™m sure it will happen somehow.Â </span></p>
<h3><strong>As a well-experienced student, do you have any tips for those just starting to code?Â </strong></h3>
<p><span data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Iâ€™m a frontend UI developer at EPAM. I work in a bigger team, developing an application relying mainly on frontend technologies and designing the user interface. I use HTML, CSS and JavaScript on a daily basis.&quot;}" data-sheets-userformat="{&quot;2&quot;:384,&quot;10&quot;:1,&quot;11&quot;:3}">I think itâ€™s important to understand that the learning process canâ€™t really be accelerated. Programming is a big challenge, not easy in the beginning. But once youâ€™ve got the hang of it and understand the logic, it all becomes clear. From that point onwards everything speeds up. <img src="https://s.w.org/images/core/emoji/13.1.0/72x72/1f642.png" alt="ğŸ™‚" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" />Â </span></p>
